Explanation

@Input()

In ChildComponent, @Input() messageFromParent allows the child to receive data from parent.

In app.component.html, we use [messageFromParent]="parentMessage" to bind data.

@Output()

In ChildComponent, @Output() messageEvent = new EventEmitter<string>() defines an event.

When the button is clicked, sendMessageToParent() emits a message.

In the parent template, (messageEvent)="receiveMessage($event)" listens for that event and triggers the receiveMessage method.

Flow

Parent → Child (via @Input())

Child → Parent (via @Output() event emitter)